article.headline: Nebraska 64, Morgan State 34
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Freshman Joe McCray scored 10 of his 12 points in a 25-3 run that Nebraska used to put away Morgan State 64-34 Monday night. Jake Muhleisen's driving layup late in the first half broke a 20-20 tie and started the decisive run. The Cornhuskers (3-1) led Morgan State (2-5) by eight points at halftime and 34-22 after Marcus Neal Jr. hit consecutive baskets to open the second half. McCray hit a pair of 3-pointers and two free throws to extend the Huskers' lead to 19. Freshman Aleks Maric's free throws with 15:36 left made it 45-23. Morgan State, which shot 24 percent, made just 1 of its first 14 field-goal attempts in the second half. Jason Dourisseau added 11 points and Maric 10 for the Huskers. Sam Brand had seven points to lead Morgan State. Nebraska won its 16th straight against non-conference opponents.
